tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE FoodPrices (
  id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  food_name VARCHAR(255),
  price DECIMAL(10, 2),
  date_of_price DATE
)

CREATE TABLE market_analysis (
  analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
  date DATE,
  market_name TEXT,
  highest_price DECIMAL,
  lowest_price DECIMAL
);

CREATE TABLE MarketAnalysis (
    id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    food_id INT,
    price DECIMAL(10,2),
    market_demand INT,
    market_supply INT
);

CREATE TABLE market_analysis (
    analysis_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    food_id INT,
    market_location VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    price_index DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
    analysis_date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (food_id) REFERENCES food_prices(id)
);

CREATE TABLE pricing_strategies (
    strategy_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    food_id INT,
    pricing_model VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    price_threshold DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
    effective_date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (food_id) REFERENCES food_prices(id)
);

CREATE TABLE affordability (
    affordability_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    food_id INT,
    affordability_score DECIMAL(5,2) NOT NULL,
    affordability_level VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    analysis_date DATE NOT NULL,
    FOREIGN KEY (food_id) REFERENCES food_prices(id)
);

CREATE TABLE FoodPrices ( 
    id INT PRIMARY KEY, 
    product_name VARCHAR(255), 
    price DECIMAL(10,2), 
    date_added TIMESTAMP, 
    store_id INT 
);

CREATE TABLE MarketAnalysis ( 
    id INT PRIMARY KEY, 
    product_id INT, 
    date_analyzed DATE, 
    market_trend VARCHAR(50), 
    price_fluctuation DECIMAL(5,2) 
);

CREATE TABLE PricingStrategies ( 
    id INT PRIMARY KEY, 
    strategy_name VARCHAR(255), 
    description TEXT, 
    start_date DATE, 
    end_date DATE 
);
